  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Activate! Integrated Social Protection and Employment to Accelerate Progress for Young People in Montenegro</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project aims to support the country in poverty reduction by using innovations to reach out and engage those left behind. The programme delivers the latest scientific methods in social protection policy making and in mobilizing young people who are on the margins of society. Innovated approaches will be introduced in two major areas: i) innovative policy making on social protection which will enable better targeted social protection, and ii) innovative practices aimed at greater engagement and social inclusion of vulnerable youth. These interventions aim to help Montenegro build well-equipped, integrated social protection and employment systems able to reach those left behind and able to offer client-oriented services so that vulnerable persons are able to cope with the challenges of poverty, inequality, unemployment and migration. The Activate! programme directly supports the government to serve the 24 per cent of the population affected by poverty and allocate 2 per cent of the annual GDP for social protection in a more cost-effective way.</narrative>
  </description>
